Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides `PipelineStage`, `ProjectConfig`, `Annotation`, `AnnotationCaptureData`
- stage_sidebar_TypeScriptReact.prompt — provides `StageSidebar`
- video_player_TypeScriptReact.prompt — provides `VideoPlayer`
- annotation_panel_TypeScriptReact.prompt — provides `AnnotationPanel`
- stage1_project_setup_TypeScriptReact.prompt through stage10_audit_TypeScriptReact.prompt — provides stage panels

Instructions
- Import all 10 stage components: `import Stage1ProjectSetup from '@/components/stages/Stage1ProjectSetup'` etc.
- Stage panel switch: `const StagePanel = STAGE_PANELS[activeStage]`. Use a `Record<PipelineStage, React.ComponentType<{ onAdvance: () => void }>>` map.
- `onAdvance` handler: increments to the next stage in the pipeline order.
- Review tab: `<VideoPlayer src={fullVideoPath} annotations={annotations} onAnnotationCapture={handleCapture} />`.
- Full video path: `/api/video/outputs/full_video.mp4`.
- `handleCapture`: POST to `/api/annotations` with `{ sectionId, timestamp, text, drawingDataUrl, compositeDataUrl, videoFile }`, then refresh annotations.
- `annotationPreFill` from Stage 10: set into VideoPlayer as initial state if available.
- Tab bar: `<div className="flex border-b border-border">` with `<button>` for each tab.
- Two-column layout: `<div className="flex h-full">` with sidebar (fixed width) and main panel (flex-1).

Deliverable
- `app/page.tsx` — root client component with tab management, stage routing, and review workflow.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- `projectConfig` is loaded once on mount; stage panels that need it receive it as a prop or refetch from the API.
- The Review tab shows the full stitched video, not individual sections.
- `annotations` are refreshed after each `onAnnotationCapture` and after batch resolve completes.

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
